extends layout

block content
  section.page-hero.page-hero--short
    .container
      h1 Food Education
      p.page-subtitle Learn about healthy eating, food growing, and how to make informed choices for you and your community.

  section.section
    .container
      .edu-grid
        //- ── Card 1: Why Healthy Eating Matters ─────────────────
        .edu-card
          .edu-card-icon
            i.fa-solid.fa-heart-pulse
          h2 Why Healthy Eating Matters
          p A balanced diet provides your body with the nutrients it needs to function properly. Eating a variety of foods rich in vitamins, minerals, and fibre helps maintain energy levels, supports immune function, and reduces the risk of chronic diseases.
          p Birmingham is home to a growing food growing movement that connects communities with local produce. With over 113 allotment sites across the city, residents can access fresh, affordable food year-round.
          .edu-stat-strip
            .edu-stat
              span.edu-stat-number 113
              span.edu-stat-label Allotment Sites
            .edu-stat
              span.edu-stat-number 7,000
              span.edu-stat-label Plots Available
            .edu-stat
              span.edu-stat-number 35,000
              span.edu-stat-label People Supported

        //- ── Card 2: Five a Day ──────────────────────────────────
        .edu-card
          .edu-card-icon
            i.fa-solid.fa-apple-whole
          h2 How to Incorporate Your Five a Day
          p Getting your recommended five portions of fruit and vegetables each day is easier than you might think. Here are some simple ideas for every meal:
          .meal-rows
            .meal-row
              .meal-icon
                i.fa-solid.fa-sun
              .meal-info
                strong Breakfast
                p Yoghurt with berries · Glass of orange juice
            .meal-row
              .meal-icon
                i.fa-solid.fa-seedling
              .meal-info
                strong Lunch
                p Mixed salad · Apple or banana on the side
            .meal-row
              .meal-icon
                i.fa-solid.fa-utensils
              .meal-info
                strong Dinner
                p Broccoli, carrots and peas with your main course
            .meal-row
              .meal-icon
                i.fa-solid.fa-cookie-bite
              .meal-info
                strong Snacks
                p Carrot sticks with hummus · Handful of grapes
          .edu-tip
            i.fa-solid.fa-lightbulb
            p
              strong Tip:&nbsp;
              | Aim for a variety of colours on your plate — each colour represents different nutrients your body needs.

        //- ── Card 3: Food Classifications ───────────────────────
        .edu-card
          .edu-card-icon
            i.fa-solid.fa-chart-pie
          h2 Food Classifications
          p Understanding the five main food groups helps you build a balanced plate. Aim to include each group in your daily diet in the right proportions.
          .food-groups-list
            .food-group-badge.badge--green
              i.fa-solid.fa-leaf
              div
                strong Fruits &amp; Vegetables
                p Vitamins, minerals &amp; fibre — aim for the largest portion
            .food-group-badge.badge--amber
              i.fa-solid.fa-wheat-awn
              div
                strong Carbohydrates
                p Bread, rice, pasta, potatoes — your main energy source
            .food-group-badge.badge--red
              i.fa-solid.fa-drumstick-bite
              div
                strong Protein
                p Meat, fish, eggs, beans, lentils — for growth and repair
            .food-group-badge.badge--blue
              i.fa-solid.fa-bottle-water
              div
                strong Dairy &amp; Alternatives
                p Milk, cheese, yoghurt — for calcium and bone health
            .food-group-badge.badge--purple
              i.fa-solid.fa-droplet
              div
                strong Fats &amp; Oils
                p Olive oil, nuts, avocado — essential in small amounts
          .edu-note
            i.fa-solid.fa-circle-info
            p Also remember to drink 6–8 glasses of water per day and limit added salt and sugar.

  //- ── Plate Guide Section ──────────────────────────────────────
  section.section.plate-section
    .container
      .plate-layout
        //- Left: Image
        .plate-image-wrap
          .plate-image-ring
            img(src='/images/healthy-eating-plate.avif', alt='The Healthy Eating Plate — food groups diagram showing Grain Foods, Vegetables and Beans, Fruits, Lean Meats Fish and Poultry, and Dairy Foods')

        //- Right: Explanation
        .plate-info
          .plate-eyebrow
            i.fa-solid.fa-circle-check
            span Visual Guide
          h2 The Healthy Eating Plate
          p This food plate diagram shows the five core food groups and the proportions you should aim to include in your daily diet. Each coloured segment represents a different group — the larger the segment, the more of that food type you should eat.
          .plate-segments
            .plate-segment
              .plate-segment-dot(style='background: #4caf50')
              div
                strong Vegetables &amp; Beans
                p Fill roughly a third of your plate — packed with fibre, vitamins, and antioxidants.
            .plate-segment
              .plate-segment-dot(style='background: #f97316')
              div
                strong Grain Foods
                p Wholegrain breads, rice, oats, and pasta — your primary source of sustained energy.
            .plate-segment
              .plate-segment-dot(style='background: #84cc16')
              div
                strong Fruits
                p Fresh, frozen, or tinned — aim for two or more servings of fruit each day.
            .plate-segment
              .plate-segment-dot(style='background: #ef4444')
              div
                strong Lean Meats, Fish &amp; Poultry
                p Choose lean cuts and include oily fish twice a week for omega-3 fatty acids.
            .plate-segment
              .plate-segment-dot(style='background: #38bdf8')
              div
                strong Dairy Foods
                p Milk, cheese, and yoghurt provide calcium for strong bones and teeth.
          .plate-cta
            i.fa-solid.fa-info-circle
            p For personalised nutrition advice, speak to your GP or a registered dietitian.

  //- ── Bottom section ───────────────────────────────────────────
  section.section.section--light-green
    .container
      .edu-bottom-grid
        //- Left: Grow Your Own
        .grow-card
          .grow-card-header
            i.fa-solid.fa-seedling
            h2 Grow Your Own – Get Involved
          p Birmingham has a thriving network of community allotments and growing spaces. Growing your own food is a great way to access fresh produce, reduce food costs, and connect with your local community.
          p Whether you have a garden, balcony, or just a windowsill, you can start growing herbs, vegetables, and fruits at home. Community allotments offer plots for those without outdoor space.
          .grow-benefits
            .grow-benefit
              i.fa-solid.fa-check
              span Fresh, nutritious produce year-round
            .grow-benefit
              i.fa-solid.fa-check
              span Reduce household food costs
            .grow-benefit
              i.fa-solid.fa-check
              span Connect with the local community
            .grow-benefit
              i.fa-solid.fa-check
              span Improve mental wellbeing through gardening

        //- Right: Useful Links
        .links-card
          .links-card-header
            i.fa-solid.fa-link
            h2 Useful Links
          p Find out more about growing your own food and Birmingham's allotment network:
          .useful-links
            .useful-link-item
              .useful-link-info
                strong Warm Earth
                p Expert gardening advice, seasonal growing guides, and community growing resources.
              a.btn.btn-green.btn-sm(href='https://www.warmearth.org.uk', target='_blank', rel='noopener noreferrer')
                i.fa-solid.fa-arrow-up-right-from-square
                |  Visit Website
            .useful-link-item
              .useful-link-info
                strong Birmingham Allotments
                p Apply for an allotment plot, find your nearest site, and join Birmingham's growing community.
              a.btn.btn-green.btn-sm(href='https://www.birmingham.gov.uk/allotments', target='_blank', rel='noopener noreferrer')
                i.fa-solid.fa-arrow-up-right-from-square
                |  Visit Website
